extendedInfo.description: New reduced price!Upward Mobility presents 337 exclusive questions to prepare you for the GBCI LEED General Associate Exam with our LEED GA Exam Prep app for Android.  Our original questions with explanatory answers were written by expert writers, and cover all topics on the exam.Features:* 337 exclusive multiple-choice questions.* Comprehensive explanations * Intuitive UI* Study Mode -- Learn at your own rate, checking each answer as you go.* Test Mode -- Get ready for the exam by taking a timed exam.Your satisfaction is important to us and we have a no questions asked refund policy for all our Android apps. We encourage you to try our application out risk free and let us know by e-mailing info@upwardpro.com if there are any issues.This app is not affiliated with the GBCI or USGBC.

reviews.title: Somewhat overpriced but good amount of questions
reviews.comment: For 10 bucks it\'s a bit overpriced but has a lot of questions. Was misleading though as the test section uses the same questions as the study section
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Hit or Miss
reviews.comment: This can be a reasonably helpful time-killer, since it gets you thinking about LEED concepts. However, it desperately needs a careful, well-informed editor to go through and revise it if it\'s going to be of any real value. A lot of the questions are very poorly worded, resulting in unproductive head-scratching and guessing.  What\'s worse, a number of the questions have incorrect answers listed as the correct responses, which seems to act against whatever potential benefit one might gain from using the app. It\'s on the right track, but this app needs a new/improved version.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: Good app. I used it to help me pass the leed exam.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great app
reviews.comment: This was a really great app, but only helped with 15 to 20%  of the exam. It should get an update with more questions. Specifically questions that focus on items covering more than one credit at a time.
reviews.author: A Google User
